Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.25,0:00:04.38,1080CN,,0,0,0,,咱作为发射直播几乎一集没落的太空叉脑残粉
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.25,0:00:04.38,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Those of us SpaceX fans that have been following the launches for a while now
Dialogue: 1,0:00:04.65,0:00:08.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,可能都已经习惯直播里那些酷炫镜头了
Dialogue: 2,0:00:04.65,0:00:08.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,will be well accustomed to seeing incredible camera shots like this
Dialogue: 1,0:00:08.96,0:00:14.41,1080CN,,0,0,0,,很多超高细节、帅得不要不要的镜头完美的展现了发射流程
Dialogue: 2,0:00:08.96,0:00:14.41,1080EN,,0,0,0,,These super high detailed shots provide a great spectacle during the launch procedure
Dialogue: 1,0:00:14.54,0:00:18.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,两级分离和科幻般的着陆过程
Dialogue: 2,0:00:14.54,0:00:18.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,stage separation and the always exciting landing procedure
Dialogue: 1,0:00:19.26,0:00:22.27,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但这些都是怎么拍的呢？
Dialogue: 2,0:00:19.26,0:00:22.27,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But how are we able to get these amazing shots?
Dialogue: 1,0:00:22.70,0:00:29.03,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这个视频我们将了解这类镜头最开始有多么的难拍
Dialogue: 2,0:00:22.70,0:00:29.03,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In this video we’re going to dive in and look at what makes a shot like this so difficult in the first place
Dialogue: 1,0:00:29.10,0:00:34.67,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我们要了解一下这些设备现在和之前是怎么用的
Dialogue: 2,0:00:29.10,0:00:34.67,1080EN,,0,0,0,,We’re also going to talk about the equipment that’s used and how it was used in the past
Dialogue: 1,0:00:35.21,0:00:42.65,1080CN,,0,0,0,,现在假设你有个相机，要拍一个六十公里外以每小时五千公里速度移动的火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:00:35.21,0:00:42.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Say you’ve got a camera and you’re trying to film a rocket that is 60km away and is moving at 5,000km/h
Dialogue: 1,0:00:42.96,0:00:49.98,1080CN,,0,0,0,,首先，一个标准的长焦镜头焦距最大可能只有1000毫米
Dialogue: 2,0:00:42.96,0:00:49.98,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Firstly, a standard telephoto lens will only have a maximum focal length of around 1,000mm
Dialogue: 1,0:00:50.22,0:00:56.21,1080CN,,0,0,0,,想要拍摄60公里外70米高的火箭，并让火箭占满整个画幅
Dialogue: 2,0:00:50.22,0:00:56.21,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In order to get a 70m tall rocket which is 60km away to fill up the entire frame you
Dialogue: 1,0:00:56.21,0:01:00.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,你需要一个至少十倍焦距的镜头
Dialogue: 2,0:00:56.21,0:01:00.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,would need a lens with a focal length of at least 10 times that
Dialogue: 1,0:01:00.11,0:01:03.69,1080CN,,0,0,0,,另外，为了拍摄平稳的跟拍画面
Dialogue: 2,0:01:00.11,0:01:03.69,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Secondly, in order to get smooth tracking shots like this
Dialogue: 1,0:01:03.84,0:01:07.68,1080CN,,0,0,0,,相机需要随着火箭的上升，非常完美地同步抬头
Dialogue: 2,0:01:03.84,0:01:07.68,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the camera needs to pan upwards in perfect sync with the rocket
Dialogue: 1,0:01:08.21,0:01:13.39,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这说着容易做着难，因为相机一丁点的运动
Dialogue: 2,0:01:08.21,0:01:13.39,1080EN,,0,0,0,,That is easier said than done because the smallest of movements done by the camera
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.50,0:01:17.45,1080CN,,0,0,0,,就会在拍摄画面上引起巨大变化
Dialogue: 2,0:01:13.50,0:01:17.45,1080EN,,0,0,0,,translate to huge movements at the other end where the rocket is
Dialogue: 1,0:01:17.82,0:01:24.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,如果你用一个普通三脚架，手动对准火箭画面，那画面是这样的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:17.82,0:01:24.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This is what it would look like if you tried to track the rocket manually using a standard tripod
Dialogue: 1,0:01:25.77,0:01:31.07,1080CN,,0,0,0,,同时如果你没有一万毫米焦距的镜头呢？那画面就是这样的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:25.77,0:01:31.07,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Now let's say you didn’t have a 10,000mm lens, here’s what that would look like
Dialogue: 1,0:01:31.87,0:01:39.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以拍这种画面，我们对精准度的需求可不是普通的三脚架加长焦镜头能满足的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:31.87,0:01:39.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,For a shot like this, we need something far more accurate and precise than just a long lens and a tripod
Dialogue: 1,0:01:39.56,0:01:43.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空叉目前有三个主发射场
Dialogue: 2,0:01:39.56,0:01:43.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,SpaceX makes use of 3 main launch facilities
Dialogue: 1,0:01:43.50,0:01:49.24,1080CN,,0,0,0,,东海岸肯尼迪航天中心LC-39A与卡纳维拉尔角LC-40
Dialogue: 2,0:01:43.50,0:01:49.24,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Launch complex 39A at the Kennedy Space Centre, complex 40 at Cape Canaveral
Dialogue: 1,0:01:49.50,0:01:54.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,西海岸加州的范登堡军事基地的LC-4E
Dialogue: 2,0:01:49.50,0:01:54.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and complex 4E at Vandenberg Air force Base in California
Dialogue: 1,0:01:54.52,0:02:00.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这些发射设施都是早在六七十年代就有的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:54.52,0:02:00.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,All of these launch facilities go way back to the early space days of the 60’s and 70’s
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.38,0:02:05.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,每个发射台一圈都有几个远距离追踪相机，它们大概长这样
Dialogue: 2,0:02:00.38,0:02:05.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Each launch pad is surrounded by several long range tracking cameras that look a little bit like this
Dialogue: 1,0:02:06.44,0:02:13.68,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这些运动追踪装置最初是军方用来追踪飞行器或导弹的
Dialogue: 2,0:02:06.44,0:02:13.68,1080EN,,0,0,0,,These are kineto tracking mounts which were first developed for use in the military to track down aircraft and missiles
Dialogue: 1,0:02:14.06,0:02:18.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,回到阿波罗的年代，当时有熟练的操作员控制这些设备
Dialogue: 2,0:02:14.06,0:02:18.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Back in the Apollo days, rigs like this would be controlled by a skilled operator to track
Dialogue: 1,0:02:18.80,0:02:22.03,1080CN,,0,0,0,,来追踪土星五号直刺苍穹的过程
Dialogue: 2,0:02:18.80,0:02:22.03,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the Saturn 5 rocket as it screamed into sky
Dialogue: 1,0:02:22.60,0:02:28.55,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当时，操作员的职责就是保持相机们对准正确方向
Dialogue: 2,0:02:22.60,0:02:28.55,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Back then, the skill of the operator was responsible for keeping the camera array pointed in the right direction
Dialogue: 1,0:02:28.72,0:02:32.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,今天，很多的追踪功能都是自动或者半自动的了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:28.72,0:02:32.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Today, a lot of the tracking functions are automated or semi-automated
Dialogue: 1,0:02:33.32,0:02:38.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这些动态追踪设备可以轻松地由任务指挥中心的操作员远程控制
Dialogue: 2,0:02:33.32,0:02:38.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,These Kineto mounts can easily be controlled remotely by an operator at mission control
Dialogue: 1,0:02:38.48,0:02:44.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,还能适配各种相机，成为世界上最贵的三脚架
Dialogue: 2,0:02:38.48,0:02:44.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,They can also take about any camera you can imagine and become the world's most expensive tripod
Dialogue: 1,0:02:44.70,0:02:49.55,1080CN,,0,0,0,,火箭公司使用相机跟拍火箭，给我们带来酷炫的直播画面
Dialogue: 2,0:02:44.70,0:02:49.55,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Rocket companies use these tracking cameras to provide great coverage of their launches
Dialogue: 1,0:02:49.74,0:02:54.70,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但这些昂贵的相机还会在上升过程中参与分析他们的火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:02:49.74,0:02:54.70,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but these expensive cameras are also used to analyze their rockets as they go through
Dialogue: 1,0:02:54.70,0:02:57.05,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而上升段往往是任务最困难的部分
Dialogue: 2,0:02:54.70,0:02:57.05,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the most difficult parts of their missions
Dialogue: 1,0:02:57.51,0:03:01.93,1080CN,,0,0,0,,NASA在追踪设备上会同时使用数字、胶片相机
Dialogue: 2,0:02:57.51,0:03:01.93,1080EN,,0,0,0,,NASA uses a mix of digital and film cameras on these mounts
Dialogue: 1,0:03:02.33,0:03:06.94,1080CN,,0,0,0,,短距离内的追踪相机会使用高速摄影
Dialogue: 2,0:03:02.33,0:03:06.94,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The short range tracking cameras make use of high speed frame rates and shutter speeds
Dialogue: 1,0:03:06.94,0:03:13.15,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这可以让火箭公司以极高的细节分析发射过程中的火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:03:06.94,0:03:13.15,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which are useful for rocket companies to analyze their rockets in great detail during the launch sequence
Dialogue: 1,0:03:13.44,0:03:19.01,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他们还会使用比如红外温度相机来测量航天器的温度
Dialogue: 2,0:03:13.44,0:03:19.01,1080EN,,0,0,0,,They also make use of some Infrared Temperature cameras to measure the heat of the spacecraft
Dialogue: 1,0:03:19.01,0:03:21.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,用于航天器再入大气燃烧的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:03:19.01,0:03:21.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,as it burns through the atmosphere on re-entry
Dialogue: 1,0:03:22.16,0:03:26.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这些相机在事故调查中也起到了重要作用
Dialogue: 2,0:03:22.16,0:03:26.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Cameras like these have played an important role in disaster investigations
Dialogue: 1,0:03:27.04,0:03:31.55,1080CN,,0,0,0,,追踪相机成功拍摄到了一块绝热瓦把哥伦比亚航天飞机砸了个洞
Dialogue: 2,0:03:27.04,0:03:31.55,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Tracking cameras were able to show that a falling piece of debris ripped a hole into
Dialogue: 1,0:03:31.55,0:03:37.77,1080CN,,0,0,0,,直接导致其在返回时解体，机组人员全部遇难
Dialogue: 2,0:03:31.55,0:03:37.77,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the Space Shuttle Columbia flight which caused it to disintegrate on re-entry, sadly killing the entire crew
Dialogue: 1,0:03:38.34,0:03:43.18,1080CN,,0,0,0,,而NASA之后也改进了流程，保证了航天飞机
Dialogue: 2,0:03:38.34,0:03:43.18,1080EN,,0,0,0,,NASA reviewed the footage and put new procedures in place to ensure that the Shuttle was safe
Dialogue: 1,0:03:43.18,0:03:45.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,再入地球大气的安全
Dialogue: 2,0:03:43.18,0:03:45.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,to re-enter the earth’s atmosphere
Dialogue: 1,0:03:46.06,0:03:51.11,1080CN,,0,0,0,,据NASA说，发射场周围还有几个胶片相机
Dialogue: 2,0:03:46.06,0:03:51.11,1080EN,,0,0,0,,According to NASA, they even have some film cameras placed around their launch sites loaded
Dialogue: 1,0:03:51.11,0:03:53.55,1080CN,,0,0,0,,每个里面都装有超过一千英尺的胶片
Dialogue: 2,0:03:51.11,0:03:53.55,1080EN,,0,0,0,,with over 1,000 feet of film each
Dialogue: 1,0:03:54.24,0:04:01.64,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当然，他们现在还有最新的相机技术，可以向全世界直播4K画面
Dialogue: 2,0:03:54.24,0:04:01.64,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Of course, they also have the latest of camera technology capable of streaming a 4K video feed live to the world
Dialogue: 1,0:04:02.11,0:04:06.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,他们正是靠这些才让我们在发射时看到如此震撼的画面
Dialogue: 2,0:04:02.11,0:04:06.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This is how we are able to view these amazingly clear shots as they are happening
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.45,0:04:09.45,1080CN,,0,0,0,,真的很不容易！
Dialogue: 2,0:04:07.45,0:04:09.45,1080EN,,0,0,0,,We really have come a long way!
Dialogue: 1,0:04:10.27,0:04:16.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,所以你们应该知道，拍摄、转播火箭起飞的镜头真的很不容易
Dialogue: 2,0:04:10.27,0:04:16.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,So there you have it, the method behind filming and broadcasting a rocket launch is actually very difficult
Dialogue: 1,0:04:16.70,0:04:21.02,1080CN,,0,0,0,,随着追踪系统技术、相机技术的进步
Dialogue: 2,0:04:16.70,0:04:21.02,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As the technology of the tracking systems and the cameras continue to improve
Dialogue: 1,0:04:21.16,0:04:24.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,我们可以看到越来越多这样的镜头
Dialogue: 2,0:04:21.16,0:04:24.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,we can look forward to seeing more amazing shots like this
Dialogue: 1,0:04:25.36,0:04:28.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,如果你还有什么问题，可以在评论区、弹幕里讨论
Dialogue: 2,0:04:25.36,0:04:28.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,If you have any questions be sure to leave them in the comments below
Dialogue: 1,0:04:29.10,0:04:35.58,1080CN,,0,0,0,,有兴趣的可以关注UP主，UP主会继续做很多航天的科普视频
Dialogue: 2,0:04:29.10,0:04:35.58,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and make sure you’re subscribed so you can join the discussion as we learn more about all things space
Dialogue: 1,0:04:36.00,0:04:40.35,1080CN,,0,0,0,,感谢观看，字幕翻译给虫，记得投币点赞收藏分享关注哦！
Dialogue: 2,0:04:36.00,0:04:40.35,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much for watching and I’ll see you in the next video
